55.9	Hopi	Hopi people	The Hopi are a federally recognized tribe of Native American people, who primarily live on the 2,531.773 sq mi (6,557.26 km2) Hopi Reservation in northeastern Arizona. The Hopi area according to the 2000 census has a population of 6,946 people. The Hopi language is one of the 30 of the Uto-Aztecan language family.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Hopi.jpg/270px-Hopi.jpg
